content:
Given a JSON data with the following structure:
{
  "animals": [
    {
      "name": "Lion",
      "species": "Panthera leo",
      "diet": "carnivore",
      "continent": "Africa"
    },
    {
      "name": "Tiger",
      "species": "Panthera tigris",
      "diet": "carnivore",
      "continent": "Asia"
    },
    {
      "name": "Giraffe",
      "species": "Giraffa camelopardalis",
      "diet": "herbivore",
      "continent": "Africa"
    },
    {
      "name": "Polar Bear",
      "species": "Ursus maritimus",
      "diet": "carnivore",
      "continent": "North America"
    }
  ]
}
Can you help me write a [JSON data] code to find out which continent has the highest number of carnivores?
